description:
In this episode, we uncover the Great Awakening. Throughout the 1700s and 1800s, many people slipped into religious lethargy, as the pressures and opportunities of the New World took priority. Two revivals would take place, which are known today as the Great Awakening. Men such as George Whitfield, Jonathan Edwards and Charles Finney were used in a powerful way to bring revival and call people back to God.

To find out more information about the Great Awakening visit our website to read our extended article. 
https://lineagejourney.com/read/the-great-awakening/
